import urllib.parse

KNOWN_EXTENSIONS = (
    'mp4', 'm4a', 'm4p', 'm4b', 'm4r', 'm4v', 'aac',
    'flv', 'f4v', 'f4a', 'f4b',
    'webm', 'ogg', 'ov', 'oga', 'ogx', 'spx', 'opus',
    'mkv', 'mka', 'mk3d',
    'avi', 'divx',
    'mov',
    'asf', 'wmv', 'wma',
    '3gp', '3g2',
    'mp3',
    'flac',
    'ape',
    'wav',
    'f4f', 'f4m', 'm3u8', 'smil'
)


def determine_ext(url):
    """ Extract the video extension from a URL, returning 'None' if no valid extension was found.
    URLs such as 'http://example.com/foo/bar.mp4/?download' can also have extensions extracted.
    """

    parsed_url = urllib.parse.urlparse(url)
    path = parsed_url.path
    filename = path.split('/')[-1]
    extension = filename.split('.')[-1].lower() if '.' in filename else None

    return extension
